request.description:
Get a cart.

## Use this in browser console:
```
var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.onreadystatechange = function () {
    if (xhr.readyState !== 4) return; {
        console.log(JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
    }
};
xhr.open('GET', '/api/storefront/carts');
xhr.send();
```

A checkout is an aggregation of multiple entities – Cart, Addresses, Shipping Options, and more.

## Use this in browser console:

```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/carts", true);
xhr.send('{"lineItems":[{"productId": {product_id}, "quantity": 1}]}');

 ```

- replace `{product_id}` with a valid `product_id`

Delete a cart by `cart_id`. Once a cart has been deleted it can not be recovered.

## Use this in browser console:

```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/carts/{cart_id}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{cart_id}` with a valid `cart_id`

Add a line item to a cart by `cart_id`.

## Use this in browser console:

```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/carts/{cart_id}/items", true);
xhr.send('{"lineItems":[{"productId": {product_id}, "quantity": 1}]}');

 ```

- replace `{cart_id}` with a valid `cart_id`
- replace `{product_id}` with a valid `product_id`

Deletes a cart line item by `cart_id` and `line_item_id`. Updates an existing, single line item in the cart.

Removing the last `line_item` in the cart deletes the cart.

## Use this in browser console:

```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/carts/{cart_id}/items/{item_id}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{cart_id}` with a valid `cart_id`
* replace `{item_id}` with a valid `line_item_id`

Get a checkout.

The `cart_id` and `checkout_id` are the same.

## Use this in browser console:

```
var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.onreadystatechange = function () {
    if (xhr.readyState !== 4) return; {
        console.log(JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
    }
};
xhr.open('GET', '/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}');
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`

Update the customer message.


## Use this in browser console:

```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("PUT", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}", true);
xhr.send('{"customerMessage": "This is a customer message!"}');
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`

Adds customer's billing address to checkout using the `checkout_id`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/billing-address", true);
xhr.send('{"billingAddress":{"firstName": "Tiffany","lastName": "Aching","email": "taching@test.com","company": "Aching Farm","address1": "1908 Home Farm Road","address2": "Apt 1","city": "Chalk","stateOrProvinceCode": "TX","countryCode": "US","postalCode": "78669"}}');
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`

Updates customer's billing address in checkout using the `checkout_id` and `address_id`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/billing-address/{address_id}", true);
xhr.send('{"billingAddress":{"firstName": "Tiffany","lastName": "Aching","email": "taching@test.com","company": "Aching Farm","address1": "1908 Home Farm Road","address2": "Apt 1","city": "Chalk","stateOrProvinceCode": "TX","countryCode": "US","postalCode": "78669"}}');
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`
* replace `{address_id}` with a valid `billing_address_id`

Removes a line item from the cart using the `checkout_id`, `cart_id` and `item_id`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/carts/{cartId}/items/{itemId}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`
* replace `{cart_id}` with a valid `cart_id`
* replace `{item_id}` with a valid `line_item_id`

Removes an existing consignment from checkout using the `checkout_id` and `consignment_id`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/consignments/{consignment_id}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`
* replace `{consignment_id}` with a valid `consignment_id`

Removes an existing coupon from checkout using the `checkout_id` and the `coupon_code`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/coupons/{coupon_code}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`
* replace `{coupon_code}` with a valid `coupon_code`

Adds gift certificate code to checkout using the `checkout_id`.

* You are not able to purchase a gift certificate with a gift certificate.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/gift-certificates", true);
xhr.send('{"giftCertificateCode": "{gift_certificate_code}"}');
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`
* replace `{gift_certificate_code}` with a valid `gift_certificate_code`

Removes an existing gift certificate from checkout using the `checkout_id` and `gift_certificate_code`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/gift-certificates/{gift_certificate_code}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`
* replace `{gift_certificate_code}` with a valid `gift_certificate_code`

Verifies if checkout is created by human using `checkout_id`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/spam-protection", true);
xhr.send('{"token": "token_string"}');
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`

Applies any available store credit to a checkout by `checkout_id`. As on the storefront, all available store credit will be used (up to the value of the order) and no amount need be specified.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/store-credit", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`

Removes store credit from a checkout by `checkout_id`.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("DELETE", "/api/storefront/checkouts/{checkout_id}/store-credit", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{checkout_id}` with a valid `checkout_id`

Get form fields.

## Use this in browser console:
```
var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.onreadystatechange = function () {
    if (xhr.readyState !== 4) return; {
        console.log(JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
    }
};
xhr.open('GET', '/api/storefront/form-fields');
xhr.send();
```

Creates or updates an email subscription.

By default, customers receive abandoned cart emails as soon as they provide their email address in the checkout flow. They can opt out using this endpoint.

However, if Store Settings > Miscellaneous > Require Consent is enabled, Abandoned Cart Emails are not sent by default, and the customer should opt-in.

## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("POST", "/api/storefront/subscriptions", true);
xhr.send('{"email": "taching@test.com","acceptsMarketingNewsletter": true,"acceptsAbandonedCartEmails": true}');
```

Returns order data by `order_id`. This will return order data immediately after an order is placed on the storefront.

## Use this in browser console:
```
var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.onreadystatechange = function () {
    if (xhr.readyState !== 4) return; {
        console.log(JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
    }
};
xhr.open('GET', '/api/storefront/orders/{order_id}');
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{order_id}` with a valid `order_id`

Get currently logged in customer.


## Use this in browser console:
```
xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open("GET", "/customer/current.jwt?app_client_id={client_id}", true);
xhr.send();
```
* replace `{client_id}` with a valid `app_client_id`

## Notes
Must be used with a client ID created through DevTools. Does not work with control panel created OAuth tokens.

